DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260327T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260327T220000
SUMMARY:Conversation in Spanish & English Practice Online
DESCRIPTION:Language Exchange Toronto - Se Habla English & Spanish\n**Span
 ish Language Conversation Toronto** is part of ***Se Habla.***\n\n“Se Ha
 bla” is a leading online community for cultural and linguistic exchange 
 where you can participate in enriching sessions\, make new friends\, and c
 onnect with a growing global network. With 9 Meetup groups across 9 cities
  in 6 countries\, Se Habla is truly open to everyone from Alaska to Patago
 nia\, and from Europe and Asia to Australia. Join us and don’t miss the 
 opportunity to practice with native speakers.\n\n**We have been meeting si
 nce June 2020 on the following days:**\n\n* Monday\n* Wednesday\n* Friday\
 n* Saturday\n* Sunday\n\nWith a one-time donation\, you can join the meeti
 ngs as many times as you like and stay as long as you wish.\n\n**Format**\
 n**Conversation Rooms (Everyday and All levels)**\nDepending on attendance
  and nationality\, small groups are formed with 4-6 people:\n\n* 2 native 
 English speakers\n* 2 native Spanish speakers\n* 1 native speaker of anoth
 er language\n\nThe meetings last for 2 hours and are divided into 4 period
 s:\n\n* 30 minutes speaking in English\n* 30 minutes speaking in Spanish\n
 * 30 minutes speaking in English\n* 30 minutes speaking in Spanish\n\n**Be
 ginner Room (Optional and only Mondays)**\nWelcome\, English and Spanish b
 eginners.\n**Check the English and Spanish lessons** **here »** [https://
 myspanishclass.xyz/](https://myspanishclass.xyz/)\n\n**Debate Room (Option
 al and only Wednesday)**\nNew topic each week.\n**Check the discussion top
 ics here »** [https://se-habla.com/category/article/](https://se-habla.co
 m/category/article/)\n\nPlease note that **we speak half of the time in En
 glish and half in Spanish.** We help each other learn both languages.\n\n*
 *After two hours**\, everyone returns to the main room to meet all partici
 pants and take a group screenshot. If you have time\, you’re welcome to 
 stay and continue the conversation for as long as you like.\n\n**Community
 **\n**We have 9 MeetUp groups meeting at the same time** (Mexico City\, Ca
 lgary\, Vancouver\, Toronto\, New York\, London\, Los Angeles\, Medellín\
 , and Santiago de Chile). However\, during the exchange\, you will meet pe
 ople not only from these cities but also from all over the world.\n\nYou c
 an get the link to our 9 MeetUp groups by visiting any of the following pa
 ges:\n[https://se-habla.com/spanish-meetup/](https://se-habla.com/spanish-
 meetup/)\n[[https://se-habla.com/english-meetup/](https://se-habla.com/eng
 lish-meetup/)\n\n**One-Time Donation**\nFor over four years\, the meetings
  were free\, but currently I am requesting a **ONE-TIME DONATION** to acce
 ss the meetings and help to cover the costs of the 9 MeetUp Groups and Zoo
 m.\n\nYou can make the one-time donation at the link below. Afterward\, Pa
 yPal will redirect you to a page where you'll find the Zoom link to join t
 he meeting.\n[https://se-habla.com/language-exchange](https://se-habla.com
 /language-exchange/)\n\nIf you have already donated and don't have the Zoo
 m link\, please contact me.\n\n**Please don’t hesitate to reach out if y
 ou have any further questions.**\n\nSee you soon\,\nHéctor Fuentes
